-- Agora, Ciech, NG2 and PGE May Be Active: Central European Equity Preview
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 2010-09-30T03:59:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/agora-ciech-ng2-and-pge-may-be-active-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in central
European markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names. Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index  added 0.5 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
declined 0.9 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  lost 0.4 percent.  Agora SA  (AGO PW): BZ WBK funds cut its stake in Poland’s
biggest publisher to 24.98 percent from 25.01 percent. Agora
lost 1.6 percent to 28 zloty.  Ciech SA  (CIE PW): The Polish chemical producer that
restructured debt to banks earlier this year called a
shareholders meeting for Oct. 28 to vote on a sale of new shares
or convertible bonds. Ciech slid 1 percent to 25.12 zloty.  NG2 SA  (CCC PW): Poland’s largest publicly traded shoe
retailer was downgraded to “sell” from “reduce” at Erste
Group Bank AG. Its shares gained 0.9 percent to 59.5 zloty.  PGE SA  (PGE PW): Poland’s largest utility signed a deal to
buy rival Energa SA from the country’s Treasury Ministry for
7.53 billion zloty ($2.59 billion). PGE shares closed unchanged
at 22.9 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
